---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Mixing" active="mixing">
  <div class="container">

    <section class="page-header">
      <h3>Analog Console</h3>
      <h1>Mixing</h1>
      <p>The Tascam Model 12 receives processed stems from the Wing. Real faders, analog EQ, hands on the console. Every mix pass captured automatically.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="vu-bar"></div>

    <section class="ruled">
      <h3>Why an Analog Console</h3>
      <div class="prose mt-sm">
        <p>
          Mixing in the box is powerful, but there's something about reaching for a fader instead of clicking a mouse. The Model 12 gives every stem its own physical channel &mdash; vocal, rhythm guitar, lead guitar, bass, drums, piano, and overdubs each get a dedicated fader with analog EQ and compression.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Wing's matrix buses serve as a permanent routing layer. Each matrix feeds a specific Model 12 channel over USB. Wire it once, and every project automatically lands on the right fader. The Wing handles effects and processing upstream; the Model 12 handles balance and tone.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ruled">
      <h3>What Lands on Each Fader</h3>
      <div class="grid-3 mt-sm">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Vocal</h4>
          <p>Processed vocal with optional doubler effect from the Wing. Outboard warmth already baked in.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Rhythm Guitar</h4>
          <p>Guitar through amp sim and outboard. RACKAMP clean tone or raw DI depending on the session.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Lead Guitar</h4>
          <p>Same outboard chain, different amp sim. ANGEL high-gain tone for leads and solos.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Bass</h4>
          <p>Logic's session player bass with optional sub-octave thickener from the Wing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Drums</h4>
          <p>Logic's session player drums in stereo. Full kit width across the mix.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Piano / Synth</h4>
          <p>Logic's session player keys in stereo. Fills out the harmonic foundation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ruled">
      <h3>Tape Saturation</h3>
      <div class="prose mt-sm">
        <p>
          Tape character is added in Logic using the T-RackS Tape Machine plugin &mdash; a Tascam 388 emulation that adds compression, harmonic saturation, and gentle frequency shaping. Each track gets its own instance with settings tuned to the instrument. By the time stems reach the Model 12, the tape character is already part of the sound.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ruled">
      <h3>The Mix Pass</h3>
      <div class="prose mt-sm">
        <p>
          Set levels, shape EQ, add compression. The Model 12 captures every mix to tracks 11 and 12 automatically &mdash; a stereo mixdown that's always recording. Try a pass, listen back, adjust, try again. Every version is saved. No bouncing, no exporting. Just press play and mix.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Model 12's main output returns to the Wing for monitoring on headphones or speakers. Solo the mix return channel to hear exactly what the Model 12 is producing, isolated from everything else.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Base>
